title: Configuration
modified: 20260331215542318

!! Introduction

All DevTools settings are controlled via TiddlyWiki configuration tiddlers. The main toggle is also available in the Control Panel under ''Settings'' &rarr; ''Source Position Tracking''.

!! Settings Overview

|! Tiddler |! Values |! Default |! Description |
|! `$:/config/wikilabs/SourcePositionTracking` |`yes` / `no` |`no` |Master switch — enables or disables all source position tracking |
|! `$:/config/wikilabs/SourcePositionTracking/ShowEditMenuItem` |`show` / (empty) |hidden |Shows "Edit at L..." in the [[Context Menu]] — opens tiddler editor with source range selected |
|! `$:/config/wikilabs/SourcePositionTracking/ShowEditInline` |`show` / (empty) |hidden |Shows "Edit inline" in the [[Context Menu]] — opens the [[Inline Editor]] popup |

!! Enabling Source Position Tracking

!!! Via Control Panel

# Open ''Control Panel'' (gear icon in the sidebar)
# Go to the ''Settings'' tab
# Find ''Source Position Tracking''
# Check the box
# ''Save and reload'' the page

!!! Via Tiddler

Set the text of `$:/config/wikilabs/SourcePositionTracking` to `yes` and reload.

!! Performance

When tracking is ''disabled'' (the default), the plugin has ''zero overhead'' — the hooks are registered but do nothing because `$tw.wiki.trackSourcePositions` is `false`.

When ''enabled'', the plugin:

* Adds `data-source-pos` attributes to every rendered element and link
* Caches line offsets, header line counts, and body offsets per tiddler
* Uses binary search (O(log n)) for character-to-line conversion
* Caches are cleared when tracking is toggled

!! Data Attributes

When tracking is enabled, the following attributes are added to DOM elements:

|! Attribute |! Description |! Example |
|! `data-source-pos` |Formatted position string |`L81-L84 @ $:/cards/procedures` |
|! `data-source-start` |Character offset of start |`1542` |
|! `data-source-end` |Character offset of end |`1698` |
|! `data-source-context` |`currentTiddler` if different from source |`MyListItem` |
|! `data-source-caller` |Transclusion caller chain |`← $:/core/ui/ViewTemplate` |

!! Widget Patches

The plugin monkey-patches several core widgets to enable tracking (no core file modifications needed):

* `setVariable` — stores `sourceTitle` for variable-to-tiddler attribution
* `importvariables` — propagates `sourceTitle` through imported globals
* `link` widget — invokes `th-dom-rendering-link` hook
* `codeblock` widget — invokes `th-dom-rendering-codeblock` hook
* `transclude` widget — sets `sourceContext` for position attribution across transclusion boundaries

